<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-10-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-10-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="437" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d437">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/977.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Minister of the Dominican
                                    Republic</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dominican Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-10-15">
                                    <hi rend="italic">October 15, 1913</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Secretary</hi>: I have the honor to inform you
                            that the Dominican Government having recovered the Province of Samaná,
                            and the state of rebellion that caused the blockade and closure of the
                            ports of Samaná and Sánchez having come to an end, those two ports have
                            again been opened to commerce and the blockade has been raised
                            there.</p>
                        <p>I avail [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Fran’co J. Peynado</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>